Ok to clarify for some of you who obviously just came to this site on ACCIDENT... NL SUBS means that there are hard coded subs from the NETHERLANDS.. RIP2DVD means that the files are ready to go onto a DVDR and do not need to be converted to .vob format first (which is the file type needed to burn to a DVD.) There are different blank media types such as DVD plus or minus R.. these are 4.7gb in space... the in this take up a little over 4gb to fill the blank DVD, so it has been converted using the best quality available to still fit on a DVD5 *the kind we buy and burn to* a DVD9 is the kind original store bought DVDs are burned to in factories.. more space better quality...unless you buy a DVD9 you can not burn straight from store bought DVD to a blank DVD5, it has to be ripped to a file (.avi which is what we like to download from here) and then converted back to .vob and then burned to the smaller DVD5... you people should honestly do some research before bitching at an uploader because you cant understand what they are saying. And I dont have a dog in this fight.. Im not the uploader and not even downloading these files..just commenting on how ridiculous non-informed people are...
